# Next.js Standards

- **Next.js 16**: App Router; Turbopack default; use `proxy.ts` instead of deprecated `middleware.ts`
- Route groups: (marketing), (forms), (auth)
- Server Components by default; `"use client"` only when needed
- Caching: opt-in with `"use cache"` directive
- Use `next/link`, `next/image`, Metadata API
- No secrets in client; `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` for public config only
- Loading/error boundaries: `loading.tsx`, `error.tsx`
- Node 20.9+; TypeScript 5.1+

```tsx
// Good: Server Component
export default async function Page() {
  const data = await fetchData();
  return <div>{data}</div>;
}

// Good: Client only when needed
"use client";
export function InteractiveForm() {
  const [state, setState] = useState();
  return <form>...</form>;
}
```
